<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-20T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-20T22:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/214: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-21T11:00:00+08:00">December 21, 1929—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 21—6:45
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1178. My 1165, December 18, 5 p.m. Following from Jacobs and Bucknell:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“December 20, 10 a.m. Referring to the alternative proposal of
                                    the Chinese delegation for consular representation on the court,
                                    telegraphed by the British Consulate General at Shanghai
                                    yesterday to the interested Senior Minister, the chief of the
                                    Chinese delegation stated today that it was an official
                                    alternative proposal. We submit that this also does not provide
                                    the necessary safeguards.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>